The Coordinator, Satellite Towns Development Department (STDD), Hon Ishaku Tanko Yamawo has inspected some road projects within the FCT satellite towns to ensure that all the contractors returned to site. The Public Relations Officer of the department, Meeme Felicia, in a statement, said STDD contractors were back on sites across the six area councils. The statement added that works were going on in Kwali, Gwagwalada, Abaji, Bwari, Kuje and AMAC ranging from roads construction to electrification of communities. “The STDD coordinator, who went round with some of  engineers, promised to make sure that all things are done appropriately and that the works are all completed on time hence the FCT Administration vowed  to do its best in making sure that all the satellites towns are provided with all the necessary amenities,” the statement read.